stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> requested: start() → WorkflowStarted
  requested --> accepted: accept [guard: rider present] / action: set driver → WorkflowTransitioned
  requested --> expired: onTimeout(afterMs) via Scheduler → WorkflowTimedOut
  accepted --> completed: finish → WorkflowTransitioned
  completed --> [*]: terminal → WorkflowCompleted
  expired --> [*]: terminal + failure → WorkflowFailed
  requested --> cancelled: cancel()
  accepted --> cancelled: cancel()
  cancelled --> [*]: → WorkflowCancelled

  note right of requested
    Example "trip" definition. States/transitions/guards/
    actions/timeouts are declarative data — the engine
    interprets them and holds no business logic.
    A real transition cancels the pending timeout timer.
  end note
